DOC.brief_summary: This study will evaluate the safety and efficacy of botulinum toxin Type A compared to placebo for the treatment of Crow's Feet Lines and Frown Lines (Facial Rhytides)
DOC.brief_title: Safety and Efficacy Study of Botulinum Toxin Type A for the Treatment of Crow's Feet Lines and Frown Lines
DOC.criteria: Moderate to severe Crow's Feet Lines and Frown Lines Have adequate vision without the use of eyeglasses to assess facial wrinkles in the mirror (contact lenses OK) Current or previous botulinum toxin treatment of any serotype Diagnosis of myasthenia gravis, EatonLambert syndrome, amyotrophic lateral sclerosis Prior facial cosmetic surgery (e.g., prior periorbital surgery, facial lift, brow lift, eyelid lift or eyebrow surgery) Facial laser or light treatment, microdermabrasion, or superficial peels within 3 months Oral retinoid therapy within one year
